         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539"><!-- p1l1-r10 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Hd1e108">Rubrica 10</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De charitate hominis ad deum</head>
            <!--rubrics 6 to partway through 10 are omitted from this manuscript-->
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e370">
              <pb ed="#B" n="6-r"/>
              <cb ed="#B" n="a"/>
              <lb ed="#B"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e374">ei me ipsum. </quote>
            </p>
            <!--confusing reference, also from John 14 but the slash suggests it is another entry -->
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e386">
               <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>
               <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e390" source="http://scta.info/resource/io14_23@1-26 http://scta.info/resource/io14_24@1-8 http://scta.info/resource/io14_27@15-20 http://scta.info/resource/io14_28@1-19">/ Iesus dixit: Siquis diligit me sermonem
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>meum seruabit: et pater meus diliget eum: et
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>ad eum veniemus et mansionem apud eum
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>faciemus. Qui non diligit me sermones 
               me<lb ed="#V" n="36" break="no"/>os non seruat. Ait <sic>sesus</sic> discipulis suis quoniam
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>morti appropinquabat. Non turbetur cor
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>vestrum neque formidet: audiuistis quia 
               di<lb ed="#V" n="39" break="no"/>xi vobis: vado et venio ad vos: si 
               diligere<lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>tis me gauderetis vtique: quia vado ad patrem </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e411">
               <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>
               <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e455">/ 15. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e415" source="http://scta.info/resource/io15_4@1-27 http://scta.info/resource/io15_5@1-23 http://scta.info/resource/io15_6@1-21 http://scta.info/resource/io15_7@1-16 http://scta.info/resource/io15_10@1-8">Ait iesus discipulis suis: Manete in
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>me et ego in vobis. Sicut palmes non potest
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>facere fructum a semet ipso nisi manserit in
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>vite: Sic nec vos nisi ini me manseritis. Ego
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>sum vitis vos palmites: qui manet in me et <!--30.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>ego in eum: hic fert fructum multum: quia 
               si<lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>ne me nihil potestis facere. Si quis in me
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>non manserit mittetur foras sicut palmes et
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>arescet: et colligent eum et in ignem mittent
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>et ardet. Si manseritis in me et verba mea in
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>vobis manserint: quodcumque volueritis 
               pe<lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>tetis et fiet vobis. Ait iesus: si precepta mea
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>seruaueritis manebitis in dilectione mea. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e449">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e495">Iacobus apostolus epistola vnica. c. 2.</ref>
            / <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e459" source="http://scta.info/resource/iac2_10@1-13">Qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>cunque totam legem obseruauerit: offenderit
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>autem in vno factus est omnium reus. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e468">
               <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e510">Iohannes apostolus et euangelista 
               episto<lb ed="#V" n="58" break="no"/>la primi. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e472" source="http://scta.info/resource/Iio4_20@1-12 http://scta.info/resource/Iio4_21@2-14 ">Siquis dixerit: diligo deum et
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>fratrem suum oderit: mendax est. Hoc 
               man<lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>datum habemus a deo: vt qui diligit deum <!--slight textual differences-->
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>diligat et patrem suum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e484"> /
       <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e527">5. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e486" source="http://scta.info/resource/Iio5_3@1-9"> Hec est.
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>charitas dei vt mandata eius custodiamus </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e492">
               <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e539">Paulus apostolus epistola ad romanos
        <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>capistolo. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e496" source="http://scta.info/resource/rom8_28@4-9">Diligentibus deum omnia 
               coope<lb ed="#V" n="65" break="no"/>rantur in bonum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e504"> /
      <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e552">Idem apostolus 
               epi<lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>stola. i. ad corinthios. c. 10.</ref>
            / <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e514" source="http://scta.info/resource/Icor10_21@1-9">Non potestis
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>mensae domini participes esse vt mense 
               de<lb ed="#V" n="68" break="no"/>moniorum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e522"> /
      <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e567">Idem epistola ad timotheum
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e524" source="http://scta.info/resource/Itim1_5@1-15">Finis precepti est charitas de corde 
               pu<lb ed="#V" n="70" break="no"/>ro et conscientia pura et fide non ficta. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-d1e533">
               <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Rd1e582">Auctor li. de for. homin. vite. ca. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-de2539-Qd1e537">Amabis
        <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>deum si illum in hoc imitaberis vt velis om
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>nibus prodesse nulli nocere: et tunc te 
               iu<lb ed="#V" n="74" break="no"/>stum virum appellabunt omnes. 
               Sequen<lb ed="#V" n="75" break="no"/>tur venerabuntur et diligent: sicque merito 
               iu<lb ed="#V" n="76" break="no"/>stus appellaberis. </quote>
            </p>
         </div>
